subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks.

Scapheremaeus baylyi


sp. nov.

differs from other members of the genus by the following combination of characters: 
1
) the deep hysterosoma without the dorsoventral flattening typical of other 

Scapheremaeus

spp. 
2
) parallel regular plicatures on dorsal circumnotogastral plate; 
3
) centrodorsal region with wavy, granulate ridges; 
4
) with 
13
pairs of notogastral setae, having only two pairs of setae in the 
h
series; 
5
) setae of 
p
series on the ventral circumnotogastral plate.
